Session of 2025
SENATE BILL No. 220
By Senators Sykes, Corson, Faust-Goudeau, Francisco, Holscher and Pettey
2-5
1 AN ACT concerning children and minors; relating to child labor;
2 increasing the penalty for unlawful employment of any person or child;
3 amending K.S.A. 38-612 and repealing the existing section.
4
5 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
6 Section 1. K.S.A. 38-612 is hereby amended to read as follows: 38-
7 612. That (a) Any person, firm or corporation employing any person or
8 child in violation of any provision of this act, or permitting or conniving at
9 such violation, shall be deemed guilty of a misdemeanor, and upon
10 conviction thereof shall be fined in a sum not less than twenty-five dollars
11 nor more than one hundred dollars, or by imprisonment in the county jail
12 for a period of not less than thirty days nor more than ninety days:
13 (1) Class A person misdemeanor, except as provided in subsections
14 (a)(2) and (a)(3);
15 (2) severity level 7, person felony upon a second conviction; and
16 (3) severity level 5, person felony upon a third or subsequent
17 conviction.
18 (b) In addition to any other criminal penalties provided by law, any
19 person convicted of a violation of this section for a second time shall pay a
20 fine in an amount of $25,000 and any person convicted of a violation of
21 this section for a third or subsequent time shall pay a fine in an amount of
22 $50,000.
23 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 38-612 is hereby repealed.
24 Sec. 3. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
25 publication in the statute book.

